The paper discusses fundamental physical layer issues in vehicular communications, including channel modeling, channel estimation, modulation techniques, and resource allocation. These topics are all related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for millimeter wave bands, which falls under the category of millimeter wave communications (cs.MM). The paper also touches on the potential for vehicular communications to improve traffic efficiency and safety, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY).
